Utilizing the inherent versatility of a field, it is possible to implement multiple cycles of sowing and harvesting within the same boundaries throughout the growing season

Utilizing the inherent versatility of a field, it is possible to implement multiple cycles of sowing and harvesting within the same boundaries throughout the growing season. Leveraging this capability, farmers can strategically devise crop plans for distinct sections of their fields and seamlessly execute those plans while maintaining the integrity of the field boundaries.

Health Map allows you to analyze your field's instant state and keep track of its growth throughout the time.Color representation in the map is as follows:
Regions with no date due to the atmospheric obstacles such as cloud, cloud shadow and haze.
For a field that has a natural growth rate , as the crops grow horizontally and cover the soil, the color of the field in the map would be brown, yellow and green, respectively.
If you are observing inconsistent colors with the expected phenological behavior of the plant, it indicates that there may be agricultural problems in that region, during these dates.
